// Dome Windows resource script.
// This is the single source of truth for resources compiled into dome.exe.
// build.rs passes this file to embed-resource, which invokes rc.exe (MSVC)
// or windres (GNU) depending on the target toolchain.

// RT_MANIFEST (type 24), ID 1 = CREATEPROCESS_MANIFEST_RESOURCE_ID.
// The Windows loader reads this ID from the EXE on process startup,
// before any DLL code runs, to set DPI awareness and other process-wide flags.
1 24 "dome.manifest"

// Application icon, numeric ID 1. Windows Explorer, taskbar, and Alt-Tab
// probe numeric icon IDs in ascending order; ID 1 is the conventional primary.
// Note: named icon resources (e.g. IDI_ICON1) are a Visual Studio convention
// defined in a local resource.h, not an SDK symbol. Using a bare identifier
// would make both rc.exe and windres treat it as a string-named resource,
// breaking the shell's numeric-ID lookup. Always use numeric literals here.
1 ICON "Dome.ico"
